      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix: backstop WhatsApp message-tool finals",
        "body": "## Summary\n- Backstop WhatsApp group/channel `message_tool_only` turns when the model returns user-facing final text without calling the message tool.\n- Preserve send-policy denial and observed-delivery checks so the backstop does not duplicate successful sends or bypass denied sessions.\n- Add regression coverage for the WhatsApp backstop and send-policy-denied case.\n\n## Reason\nA live OpenClaw 2026.6.6 Koro WhatsApp group turn produced final text but did not call `message(action=\"send\")`. The installed runtime then hit a delivery-layer path that threw `ReferenceError: sendFollowupPayloads is not defined`, causing inbound processing to fail and keeping the answer private. A local installed-dist hotfix is in place, but this source PR is the durable path so future OpenClaw updates/releases preserve the behavior.\n\n## Verification\n- `node scripts/test-projects.mjs src/auto-reply/reply/dispatch-from-config.reply-dispatch.test.ts src/auto-reply/reply/private-message-tool-final.test.ts`\n  - Passed 2 Vitest shards\n  - 17 tests passed\n\n## Release notes\n- Fixes missed visible replies for WhatsApp group/channel `message_tool_only` turns where the agent returns final text without using the message tool.\n\n## Risks\n- Low: scoped to WhatsApp group/channel `message_tool_only` final replies with no observed message-tool delivery and no send-policy denial.\n- Local note: Henry's active 6.6 install has a temporary dist hotfix until an updated OpenClaw build containing this PR is installed.\n",
